bug.short_desc: Problem using ibus-typing-booster in firefox: When typing "word . " the space between "word" and ". " is not deleted and the cursor ends up after "word "
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1225303 problem-when-typing-punctuation-in-firefox.ogv
[mfabian@Fedora-Workstation-netinst-x86_6 ~]$ cat /etc/fedora-release Fedora release 25 (Twenty Five) [mfabian@Fedora-Workstation-netinst-x86_6 ~]$ rpm -q ibus-typing-booster ibus-typing-booster-1.5.14-1.fc25.noarch [mfabian@Fedora-Workstation-netinst-x86_6 ~]$
When typing “word . ” in gedit (or any other gnome program), the result is “word. ” and the cursor is after the final space. I.e. the automatic deletion of the space between “word” and “.” using surrounding text works correctly in gedit and other gnome programs.
In Qt and X11 programs, surrounding text is not supported. Therefore, in Qt and X11 programs the result of typing “word . ” is “word . ” with the cursor positioned after the final space. That is the best one can do when surrounding text is not supported.
In firefox however, the result of typing “word . ” is “word .” and the cursor is positoned *before* the final “.”. I.e. one space is deleted, but the wrong one. And the cursor ends up in a weird position.
See attached video.
